==English==

===Etymology===
From {{F.}} {{term|automatique}}, from {{Gr.}} {{term|αυτοματικός|sc=Grek|tr=automatikos}}, from {{AGr.}} {{term|αυτόματον|sc=polytonic|tr=automaton}}, neuter of {{term|αυτόματος||selfmoving, moving of oneself, self-acting, spontaneous|sc=polytonic|tr=automatos}}, from {{term|αυτός||self, myself|sc=polytonic|tr=autos}} + {{term|μέμαα||to wish eagerly, strive, yearn, desire|sc=polytonic|tr=memaa}}. {{rfscript|Grek <!-- shouldn't there be smooth breathing marks or something? -->}}

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˌɔːtəˈmætɪk/}}, {{SAMPA|/%O:t@"m{tIk/}}
* {{audio|en-us-automatic.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*: Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ætɪk|-ætɪk]]

===Adjective===
{{en-adj|-}}

# Capable of operating without external control or intervention.
#: ''The '''automatic''' clothes washer was a great labor-saving device''
# Acting out of habit; without conscious thought.
#: ''My reaction of fear was '''automatic'''.''
# {{context|of a [[firearm]] such as a [[machine gun]]}} Firing continuously as long as the trigger is pressed and [[ammunition]] is not exhausted.
# {{context|computing|of a local [[variable]]}} Being added and removed from the [[stack]] automatically during the course of [[function]] [[call]]s.

